  schema:name "Postliberal Grammar: The Shape Crisis Takes" ;
  schema:description "A politician declares that the nation has lost its way. They name a community of authentic values. They identify an enemy who has corrupted the community. They reframe present suffering as sacrifice. They promise destiny. They assert inevitability." ;
